The ACLU has filed a lawsuit in an attempt to preserve birthright citizenship. In their filing, they used the phrase "all future persons". This phrase implies that lawsuits can be filed on behalf of people who are not yet born. If a court rules in favor of the ACLU, that means that lawsuits can be filed against women attempting to abort and abortion clinics. The plaintiff can cite this ACLU case stating that a US court recognized the personhood of those not yet born, and injunctions can then be filed which would prevent an abortion from taking place. 

So this puts the left in a pickle. Does the dem party choose to defer to the screeching women who want to kill their babies and allow birthright citizenship to go away which would mean children of illegals would be deported, or do the dems in DC allow abortion access to be put in jeopardy by allowing a court to recognize rights of people who are not yet born?
